<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="348" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,537,1177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,573,600]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Facial carinae arched (lateral view), fusiform and forming broad scutellum (frontal view); antennae flattened but not foliaceous, laterally expanding from the base to the apex having a incrassate shape (
<figureCitation box="[1295,1361,610,636]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1761,1786]" captionTargetBox="[208,1376,1190,1742]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[208,1376,1190,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. General scheme of antennal segment morphology present in Lophotettix species, highlighting the incrassate shape and the apical last segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491590" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491590/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), with 11 segments (with a distinguishable acute apical segment) and the latter segment is pale; pronotum not towards the front of the head, compresso-cristated median carina or a leaf-like crest (
<figureCitation box="[954,1053,682,708]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1937,1962]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[165,1422,166,1918]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lophotettix alticristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491592/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Figs. 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1064,1100,682,708]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1947,1972]" captionTargetBox="[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[161,1425,166,1927]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Lophotettix brevicristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 2 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491594/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1111,1148,682,708]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[167,1420,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lophotettix hancocki (Bruner, 1910) male holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/ Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491596/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1159,1195,681,708]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1939,1964]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,166,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[164,1422,166,1920]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lophotettix unicristatus Hancock, 1909 female holotype. (A) habitus in left lateral view, (B) habitus in dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 1 mm. Photo of type: Museum of Oxford University/James Hogan, photo of label and frontal view: Josef Tumbrinck." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491598/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">5A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1206,1243,682,709]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1913,1938]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,1350,1869]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1437,1350,1869]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Lophotettix zumbadoi Barranco, 2010 right lateral view of holotype. Photo of type: Pablo Barranco." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3491600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3491600/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">6A</figureCitation>
), in some species translucent, punctate when held against the light; fore and middle femurs carinated; hind femur robust, carinated and/or with lappets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,537,1177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,789,816]" pageId="2" pageNumber="348">Composition</emphasis>
